Initializes Quadtree bounds is the initial bounds (if known) maxDepth is the depth limit maxChildren is the count of leaf nodes when the split happens minDist is the smallest unit size (internally floating point coords are converted to int units for speed)Find all elements within specified bounding boxFind all elements within radius r around point pFind all elements within radius r around point p (without actual filtering by distances, so it can return false positives)Find element's index (or -1 if not found)Expand tree so it fully covers specified bounding boxExpand tree so it fully covers specified pointAdd single element (and return its index)Add multiple elements at onceDelete element by its index (use find if index is unknown)

Imports

vectors, smallseq, freeseq

Types

Vec2Provider = concept q
    q.pos is Vec2
BBoxProvider = concept q
    q.bbox is BBox2
Quadable = concept q
    ==(q, q) is bool
    q is BBox2 | Vec2 | BBoxProvider | Vec2Provider
Index = int32
Quadtree[E] = object
  data: fseq[E]
  bounds: BBox2i
  eltNodes: fseq[QuadEltNode]
  nodes: seq[QuadNode]
  freeNode: Index
  scale: float
  maxDepth: int
  maxChildren: int
